12/03/2007
ANKARA, Turkey -- Prosecutors have indicted a 10th suspect in connection with the January 19th murder of Turkish Armenian journalist and rights activist Hrant Dink.
The suspect, identified as Osman Altay, had been questioned and released by police a week earlier.
In other news, a Kurdish militant was killed when his band of fighters attacked a Turkish military unit in a mountainous area of the southeastern province of Sirnak, local media reported on Friday (March 9th).
In a separate incident, three village guards died in a gunfight with Kurdistan Workers Party terrorists in Siirt province, near the border with Iraq.
(AFP, Reuters - 09/03/07)
